  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">BenchMarks Foundation Churches</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Community stories will gain more prominence in mainstream media; community voices will be strengthened as they are supported to bring their stories in an effective way to challenge powerful corporations; BMF will become a stronger, more strategic advocacy organisation with a maintained if not increased profile in the face of conservative backlash.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will support the communications and advocacy capacity of a strong partner organization. The post-holder will coordinate the overall media strategy: she/he will develop and coordinate the publishing plan; support key branch staff in media relations; oversee development of support publications when there is a major report; coordinate with community programme; manage press releases and press responses; manage online tools e.g. website, social media etc.; develop strategies to raise BMF visibility; train community activists and interns in use of media.</narrative>
  </description>
